e, England, United Kingdom"},"zh":{"1375–1400":"1375年–1400年","1361–1418":"1361年–1418年","1400–1464":"1400年–1464年","1350–1407":"1350年–1407年","1400":"1400年","1464":"1464年","1375":"1375年","1350":"1350年","1361":"1361年","1391":"1391年","1407":"1407年","1418":"1418年","Wiltshire, England":"英國英格蘭維爾爾","lifeSummary":"Joan Childrey是Thomas Childrey的女兒，於1375年出生在英國英格蘭維爾爾。她於1391年與Thomas Calston在英國英格蘭維爾爾結婚。他們至少是1個女兒的父母。她去世於1400年在她的家鄉享年25歲。"},"zh-hans":{"1375–1400":"1375年–1400年","1361–1418":"1361年–1418年","1400–1464":"1400年–1464年","1350–1407":"1350年–1407年","1400":"1400年","1464":"1464年","1375":"1375年","1350":"1350年","1361":"1361年","1391":"1391年","1407":"1407年","1418":"1418年","Wiltshire, England":"英国英格兰維爾爾","lifeSummary":"Joan Childrey是Thomas Childrey的女儿，于1375年出生在英国英格兰維爾爾。她于1391年与Thomas Calston在英国英格兰維爾爾结婚。他们至少是1个女儿的父母。她去世于1400年在她的家乡享年25岁。"},"hr":{"1375–1400":"1375.–1400.","1361–1418":"1361–1418","1400–1464":"1400.–1464","1350–1407":"1350–1407","1400":"1400.","1464":"1464","1375":"1375.","1350":"1350","1361":"1361","1391":"1391.","1407":"1407","1418":"1418","Wiltshire, England":"Wiltshire, Engleska, United Kingdom"},"cs":{"1375–1400":"1375–1400","1361–1418":"1361–1418","1400–1464":"1400–1464","1350–1407":"1350–1407","1400":"1400","1464":"1464","1375":"1375","1350":"1350","1361":"1361","1391":"1391","1407":"1407","1418":"1418","Wiltshire, England":"Wiltshire, Anglie, United Kingdom"},"da":{"1375–1400":"1375–1400","1361–1418":"1361–1418","1400–1464":"1400–1464","1350–1407":"1350–1407","1400":"1400","1464":"1464","1375":"1375","1350":"1350","1361":"1361","1391":"1391","1407":"1407","1418":"1418","Wiltshire, England":"Wiltshire, England, United Kingdom"},"nl":{"1375–1400":"1375–1400","1361–1418":"1361–1418","1400–1464":"1400–1464","1350–1407":"1350–1407","1400":"1400","1464":"1464","1375":"1375","1350":"1350","1361":"1361","1391":"1391","1407":"1407","1418":"1418","Wiltshire, England":"Wiltshire, Engeland, Verenigd Koninkrijk"},"en":{"1375–1400":"1375–1400","1361–1418":"1361–1418","1400–1464":"1400–1464","1350–1407":"1350–1407","1400":"1400","1464":"1464","1375":"1375","1350":"1350","1361":"1361","1391":"1391","1407":"1407","1418":"1418","Wiltshire, England":"Wiltshire, England, United Kingdom","nameMeanings":[{"name":"Childrey","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["English: habitational name from Childrey in Oxfordshire, which is named for Childrey Brook. This is probably ‘stream (Old English <i>rīth</i>) of <i>Cilla</i> (masculine) or <i>Cille</i> (feminine)’, but the first element could alternatively be Old English <i>cille</i> ‘spring’. The surname has died out in England."],"variants":[{"name":"Childree","meanings":["English: variant of   Childrey  ."]},{"name":"Childre","meanings":["English: variant of   Childrey  ."]}]},{"name":"Joan","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Contracted form of Old French <i>Jo(h)anne</i>, from Latin <i>Io(h)anna</i> (  see  Joanna  ). In England this was the usual feminine form of   John   from the Middle English period onwards and was extremely popular, but in the 16th and 17th centuries it steadily lost ground to   Jane .  It was strongly revived in the first part of the 20th century, partly under the influence of  George Bernard Shaw's  play St Joan (  1923 ), based on the life of  Joan of Arc  (  1412–31 ). Claiming to be guided by the voices of the saints, she persuaded the French dauphin to defy the occupying English forces and have himself crowned, and she led the French army that raised the siege of Orleans in  1429 . The following year she was captured by the Burgundians and sold to the English, and a year later she was burned at the stake for witchcraft at the age of 18 or 19. Her story has captured the imagination of many writers, and she is variously portrayed as a national and political hero, a model of apolitical straightforwardness and honesty, and a religious heroine. She was canonized in  1920 . More recent influences have included the American film actress  Joan Crawford  (  1908–77 , born  Lucille le Sueur ), the British actress  Joan Collins  (  b. 1933 ), the American comedienne  Joan Rivers  (  b. 1933 ), and the West Indian pop singer  Joan Armatrading  (  b. 1950 )."],"variants":[{"name":"John","meanings":["New Testament: ‘God is gracious’.  See  <b>John</b> ."]}]}],"lifeSummary":"Joan Childrey was born in 1375, in Wiltshire, England, United Kingdom as the daughter of Thomas Childrey. She married Thomas Calston in 1391, in Wiltshire, England, United Kingdom. They were the parents of at least 1 daughter. She died in 1400, in her hometown, at the age of 25."},"et":{"1375–1400":"1375–1400","1361–1418":"1361–1418","1400–1464":"1400–1464","1350–1407":"1350–1407","1400":"1400","1464":"1464","1375":"1375","1350":"1350","1361":"1361","1391":"1391","1407":"1407","1418":"1418","Wiltshire, England":"Wiltshire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom"},"fi":{"1375–1400":"1375–1400","1361–1418":"1361–1418","1400–1464":"1400–1464","1350–1407":"1350–1407","1400":"1400","1464":"1464","1375":"1375","1350":"1350","1361":"1361","1391":"1391","1407":"1407","1418":"1418","Wiltshire, England":"Wiltshire, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta"},"fr":{"1375–1400":"1375–1400","1361–1418":"1361–1418","1400–1464":"1400–1464","1350–1407":"1350–1407","1400":"1400","1464":"1464","1375":"1375","1350":"1350","1361":"1361","1391":"1391","1407":"1407","1418":"1418","Wiltshire, England":"Wiltshire, Angleterre, Royaume-Uni","lifeSummary":"Joan Childrey est née en 1375, à Wiltshire, Angleterre, Royaume-Uni, fille de Thomas Childrey. Elle a épousé Thomas Calston en 1391, à Wiltshire, Angleterre, Royaume-Uni. Ils ont eu au moins 1 fille. Elle est décédée en 1400, dans sa ville natale, à l’âge de 25 ans."},"de":{"1375–1400":"1375–1400","1361–1418":"1361–1418","1400–1464":"1400–1464","1350–1407":"1350–1407","1400":"1400","1464":"1464","1375":"1375","1350":"1350